clause.text:
consulates, attorneys, and legal service providers capable of providing free legal advice or
			 representation regarding child welfare, child custody determinations, and
			 immigration matters;

paragraph.text:
notify the child welfare agency with jurisdiction over the child if the child’s parent or primary
			 caregiver is unable to make care arrangements for the child or if the
			 child is in imminent risk of serious harm;

clause.text:
if such arrangements are unavailable or the individual is unable to make such arrangements, is
			 informed of the care arrangements made for the child and of a means to
			 maintain communication with the child;

absent medical necessity or extraordinary circumstances, is not transferred from such facility
			 unless necessary to facilitate participation in child welfare proceedings;
			 and

paragraph.text:
prominently post in a manner accessible to detainees and visitors and include in detainee handbooks
			 information on the protections of this Act as well as information on
			 potential eligibility for parole or release;

subparagraph.text:
able to participate fully, and to the extent possible in-person, in all family court proceedings
			 and any other proceedings that may impact their right to custody of their
			 children;

provided access to United States passport applications or other relevant travel document
			 applications for the purpose of obtaining travel documents for their
			 children;
